http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.@value:
Address is the main concept for a contact.  It has been designed to represent any type of address in the world, including India and the UK.  For example, the property hasBuilding is important in many UK and Indian addresses to further identify the person or business location.

Street information is divided into separate properties to fully indentify direction (hasStreetDirection), Type (hasStreetType), etc.  See the associated list of properties for more.
Different type for home, office, cottage, etc.
HoursOfOperation class provides the ability to define when the contact "opens" and "closes". Used for businesses.
Properties that define the hours of operation of the contact.
PhoneNumber is another core class. It is divided into country code, and phone number.
Types of phoned include home, cell, work, etc.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: Specifies the day of the week, e.g., Monday, that the times apply to.  This is the default for that day and can be overidden by the "hasDate" property.
hasAddress links any class to the Address class.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.@value: The building where the address is located.  Often used in countries like England, India and Japan.
The section of the city where the address is located.  Often used in countries like England, India and Japan.
Specifies the opening and closing times for a specific date.  For example, used to provide times for a holiday which deviates from the norm.
Closet street intersection for the organization.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: Created for organizational purposes, to identify data properties imported from geoSPARQL.
Created for organizational purposes, to identify the object properties imported by geoSPARQL.
Created for organizational purposes, to identify the classes imported from geoSPARQL.
A property intended to relate non-spatial objects (e.g. activities) to a location(s) in space.

http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/descript.@value: Ontology to capture concepts related to contact information (addresses, phone numbers). Reuses the iContact Ontology.
